rComments: the groupwork in this course actually had a purpose and the lecture material was structured so that you're working things out with your peers rather than being talked at a lot. the assignments were interesting and you could work things around your schedule. Class was fun to attend and he is always up to discussing your mark and being fair about it

Literally I would take any class he teaches. Such a fair marker and really understands the student struggle. Sometimes I doubt my intelligence at uni but then I get a prof like him and I remember why I enjoy school and why I'm here. If you actually try and do the work, theres no way you can get lower than a 70.
Scoville is great and is really accessible if you use him as a resource! Happily taking other courses of his.

actually TEACHES the course and doesnt lecture, first course where i found group work to be helpful bc he structures it so it's productive no matter who you're working with, hes super chill w assignment help/deadlines, generally knows what hes talking about , v encouraging, stand up dude all around i wish he taught more courses mans a real G

An absolutely amazing professor. Despite not needing to attend class, his infectious positive and passionate personality will drive you to attend every lecture. The course content itself is a little dry as it is a survey course, however, he keeps it interesting with neat facts and humor.

Absolutely loved this prof! He's got such interesting insights into all the literature he has us read, and always goes in-depth onto the topic. I want to take all his classes. Beware of his teaching style though; he doesn't post slides (he doesn't have them in the first place), so you have to show up to class!

He is extremely knowledgeable and very insightful when analyzing any text. Through him, one becomes better at reading and making connections. His lectures are extremely engaging and always interesting. If you see him at his office hours, he is very friendly and will talk to you about anything. His grading is likely the most straightforward.

Professor Scoville is a real character. His lectures aren't mandatory but I always went because he's an animated lecturer. He has sung, acted out plays, read in old english- he really captivates you. He doesn't like exams, so thats a huge plus. The work load was standard if not a little light. I would defiantly tae another class with him.

Professor Scoville's lectures are so intresting and he really makes you think about what you've read. His passion is evident and contagious. His class was amazing. I would DEFINITELY take another class with him.

Professor Scoville made me fall in love with English. I literally dropped all my pre-conceived plans and traded them in for a specialization in English. He's a wonderful lecturer, very engaging, has exceptional energy and is able to command your attention and interest easily. He's absolutely adorable, and I miss his corduroy pants :')

Probably my favourite professor ever. He's very passionate about what he teaches and it shows. He goes out of his way to care for students, and it only adds to his great personality. I would highly recommend him.

Prof. Scoville is one of my favorite profs. He's super interesting and very into what he is teaching. He's great at teaching heavy material because he makes it seem like what you're reading is better than it actually is. He is a very animated person and I love going to his lectures.
Scoville is such a nice man.   You can just tell when he talks.  He's light and interesting when talking about subjects.  He makes you want to pay attention.  The only class that I've never skipped.

I loved his classes, such a great prof, and nerdy too so if you go to office hours and want to talk Marvel or Doctor Who with him he'll be prepared. Def take his classes, I had him many times and each class was a delight!

The lectures are really well done and easy to follow along while taking notes. He is really enthusiastic about the course material so you get excited. The tutorials are a little pointless since the prof explains everything so well, you get all your ideas from lectures. I would take any class of his again and I would recommend his class to anyone!

Absolutely one of the best profs I've had. Very organized, passionate about what he teaches, and can make the not-so-exciting readings very interesting. Be prepared to work and do your readings as he is not the easiest grader. Overall, highly recommended.

Scoville is a great speaker and very clear during lectures. He does a good job at thoroughly covering texts and explaining expectations. I found most of the material interesting. However, the reading pace was fast (especially if you have other heavy reading courses), making it hard to understand important text details. Overall, recommend.

Extremely organized professor, be prepared to do reading as he engages the class in discussions and asks questions. Bring your textbook or print out to class everyday as he almost always reads passages. Overall really nice and he grades fairy. Glad I took this course.

He is enthusiastic about the material, however he is a very hard marker. He is not as available for extra help as he claims to be and I found it awkward to communicate with him one-on-one. He got annoyed at the lack of interest from the students and took it out on the final papers, which he graded unfairly.
After having him for an amazing Science Fiction class I specifically chose to take Rhetoric because of him. He is an awesome prof who is enthusiastic and fun with his lectures.

A very nice prof, he is into group work,so be prepared to share with the groups and interact a lot in small groups. He is helpful and approachable! The course is not difficult, he is fair with marks. Overall, his teaching is good and it is a good experience.
Amazing Professor. He is extremely enthusiastic. He is really knowledgeable. He made my mornings great. He is the best English prof at UTM.
One of the best english professors I have had. He knows his stuff and teaches the class in a well organized manner

He's a great prof. His lectures are interesting. This is actually an easy course to take in the summer. If you need a gpa booster this is the one I'd recommend. He's helpful, he want's you to do well. A good course to take if you need improve your essay writing skills. Final exam was easy breezy. His assignments are not hard and is marked fairly.

A great prof! Coming from a pure science background, I found this course both helpful and interesting. He is very enthusiastic about what he does and presents lectures/topics in a fun, interactive manner. Overall a great prof!

The absolute best professor in the English department! His lectures are clear, he speaks in our language, and he is very excited and enthusiastic about the material. He can make boring stuff seem really cool! Definitely my favourite Prof!
Thankfully a professor of rhetoric that also practices it. Do not hesitate to take any of his classes. Note his TA's are tough markers - review it with him to make sure that it is fair.
Easily my favorite professor. I've taken a few classes with him, specifically BECAUSE of him. He makes even uninteresting material interesting.

Both highly informative and amusing, his classes are often pleasurable and always helpful when assignment time rolls around. However, his deragatory remarks about other interests and (as a consequence) the people that embrace those interests, is very disheartening and mildly insulting.
Great proffesor and loves teaching his students. Great sense of humor and helps you enjoy reading the texts. Hard marker but if you follow his lectures your golden
Awesome class--and he looks like Seth Rogan with glasses! Seriously though, great course

Professor Scoville is one of my favourite profs. His lectures are awesome and he is very passionate about the aterial and making sure you understand it. I've had him for 2 classes already and hopefully can take another one of his classes next year!
Great prof. Take his class if you get the chance.

I really liked this professor.  Lectures and required readings were very interesting.  I also liked the marks distrobution (4 essays, no exam).  The marking was fair and he was always available to answer questions.  I would definitely take this course again!
I really liked Scoville. He is funny and smart and makes the course material seem much more interesting. I would not hesitate to take another one of his class.
He is a good teacher over all he really is dedicated and he is very smart. However he or his TA is a crazy hard marker for essays!
Really takes the course material and puts it on a level that everyone can understand and uses examples of every day life that people can relate to. Does a great job at getting the class involved

One word: wow!  Very great guy who is emotionally and intellectually gifted in his field.  What a dedicated teacher. Generates stimulated and a broad spectrum of conversation. He is fun, witty, et ist a smarte man. (So much for my attempt at middle English).
Great guy all around.  Very approachable and his lectures are interesting and easy to follow.  Not a bad marker either! Not much more you can ask for!

Clarity in lectures doesn't get much better than this.
